(5, 3, '2012-08-21 22:56:06', '2012-08-21 22:56:06', '<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h1>\r\n<h1><strong>About Us</strong></h1>\r\nWe believe that each woman has the right to decide for herself the direction of her life according to her values and needs.\r\n\r\nWe provide shelter and services to women seeking safety from:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Abuse in their relationship</li>\r\n	<li>Recent survivors of sexual assault</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nServices are free of charge and are funded by Ministry of Housing and Social Development.\r\n\r\nBecoming a <em><strong>Society Member</strong> </em>is an excellent way to show your support for the programs that we provide.  Your membership is <em><strong>free</strong></em> of charge and all you need to do is complete the Society Membership Application <em>(click on link below)</em> and mail it to us at\r\n\r\nVernon Women\'s Transition House Society\r\nAdministration Office\r\n2400 46th Avenue\r\nVernon, BC V1T 9N5\r\n\r\n<em>All Society Memberships are subject to approval by our Board of Directors.</em>  Society Memberships help to maintain funding for the valuable programming we offer to women and children.  Becoming a Society Member also allows you one vote at our Annual General Meeting that takes place in June of each year.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/SocietyMembershipFrm.pdf\">Society Membership Form</a>\r\n\r\nIf you would like to know a little more about how the Vernon Women\'s Transition House Society began, please click on the link below.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/VWTHSHistory2013.pdf\">HISTORY OF VERNON WOMEN\'S TRANSITION HOUSE SOCIETY</a>\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/wsImRe3iC5k?feature=player_detailpage\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>', 'About Us', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2016-03-24 21:30:57', '2016-03-24 21:30:57', '', 0, 'http://localhost/transition-house/?page_id=5', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(1432, 2, '2015-09-25 19:21:02', '2015-09-25 19:21:02', '<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"></h1>\r\n<h1><strong>About Us</strong></h1>\r\nWe believe that each woman has the right to decide for herself the direction of her life according to her values and needs.\r\n\r\nWe provide shelter and services to women seeking safety from:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Abuse in their relationship</li>\r\n	<li>Recent survivors of sexual assault</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nServices are free of charge and are funded by Ministry of Housing and Social Development.\r\n\r\nBecoming a <em><strong>Society Member</strong> </em>is an excellent way to show your support for the programs that we provide.  Your membership is <em><strong>free</strong></em> of charge and all you need to do is complete the Society Membership Application <em>(click on link below)</em> and mail it to us at <strong>VWTHS, PO Box 625, Vernon BC, V1T 6M6</strong>. <em> All Society Memberships are subject to approval by our Board of Directors.</em>  Society Memberships help to maintain funding for the valuable programming we offer to women and children.  Becoming a Society Member also allows you one vote at our Annual General Meeting that takes place in June of each year.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/SocietyMembershipFrm.pdf\">SocietyMembershipFrm</a>\r\n\r\nIf you would like to know a little more about how the Vernon Women\'s Transition House Society began, please click on the link below.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/VWTHSHistory2013.pdf\">HISTORY OF VERNON WOMEN\'S TRANSITION HOUSE SOCIETY</a>\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/wsImRe3iC5k?feature=player_detailpage\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-25 19:21:02', '2015-09-25 19:21:02', '', 5, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2015/09/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(7, 3, '2012-08-21 22:56:15', '2012-08-21 22:56:15', '<h1>PROGRAMS &amp; SERVICES</h1>\r\n<h1>We believe that each woman has the right to decide for herself the direction of her life according to her values and needs.</h1>\r\nWe provide shelter and services to women seeking safety from:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Abuse in their relationship</li>\r\n	<li>Recent survivors of sexual assault</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe provide the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Safe shelter and support</li>\r\n	<li>Child support activities and where possible, child care</li>\r\n	<li>Meals and laundry facilities</li>\r\n	<li>Recreational opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Transportation to appointments</li>\r\n	<li>Accompaniment to appointments</li>\r\n	<li>Referrals to community services</li>\r\n	<li>Donations of clothing and household goods, when available</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nServices are free of charge and are funded by Ministry of Housing and Social Development.', 'Programs & Services', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'programs-services', '', '', '2013-11-27 18:55:06', '2013-11-27 18:55:06', '', 0, 'http://localhost/transition-house/?page_id=7', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(9, 3, '2012-08-21 22:56:23', '2012-08-21 22:56:23', '<h1>Safe Shelter</h1>\r\nAt the Transition House we provide shelter and services to women seeking safety from:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Abuse in their relationship</li>\r\n	<li>Recent survivors of sexual assault</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nConfidential services are free of charge and are funded by BC Housing.\r\n\r\nView the <a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/womens_safety_booklet.pdf\">When a Woman is Being Abused — What you Should Know and How to Help</a> booklet.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/FAQ-website.pdf\">Frequently Asked Questions</a>', 'Safe Shelter', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'safe-shelter', '', '', '2013-05-09 20:32:03', '2013-05-09 20:32:03', '', 0, 'http://localhost/transition-house/?page_id=9', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(11, 3, '2012-08-21 22:56:34', '2012-08-21 22:56:34', '<h1>Volunteer</h1>\r\nIf you are a reliable, nonjudgmental and patient person, we would like to invite you to join our team of caring volunteers. If you have recently accessed our programs, we ask that you wait two years prior to offering your services (each situation will be assessed individually).\r\n<h2>Volunteers assist us in the following areas:</h2>\r\n• Donation Garage (sorting, sizing, etc.)\r\n• Teaching special skills (yoga, tai chi, crafts, etc.)\r\n• Supervising and supporting computer use\r\n• Child Minding\r\n• Sharing talents, such as massage, esthetics, etc.\r\n\r\nAll volunteers will go through a screening interview and will be required to undergo a Criminal Record Check.', 'Volunteer', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'volunteer', '', '', '2015-06-15 22:12:58', '2015-06-15 22:12:58', '', 0, 'http://localhost/transition-house/?page_id=11', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(13, 3, '2012-08-21 22:56:42', '2012-08-21 22:56:42', '<h1></h1>\r\n<h2>Local Resources</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vernonfrc.ca/\">Family Resource Centre Society for the North Okanagan</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://fnfcvernon.com/\">First Nations Friendship Centre (North Okanagan)</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.interiorhealth.ca/Pages/default.aspx\">Interior Health</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://noccs.ca/\">North Okanagan Child Care Society</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nona-cdc.com/\">NONA Child Development Centre</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.noyfss.org/\">North Okanagan Youth and Family Services</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.rdno.ca/index.php/services/community-services/victims-assistance\">Police Based Victim Assistance (North Okanagan)</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vdiss.com/\">Vernon and District Immigrant Services Society</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://vernon-northokanagan.bc.rcmp-grc.gc.ca/ViewPage.action?siteNodeId=1019&amp;languageId=1&amp;contentId=-1&amp;categoryId=443\">Vernon/North Okanagan RCMP</a>\r\n<h2>Regional Transition Houses</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kamloopsy.org/docs/vawiss_services.pdf\">Kamloops YWCA Women’s Shelter</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kelownawomensshelter.ca/\">Kelowna Women’s Shelter</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://revelstokewomensshelter.com/\">Revelstoke Women’s Transition House</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.safesociety.ca/\">Salmon Arm Family Emergency Society</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sowins.com/\">South Okanagan Women in Need Society (Penticton)</a>\r\n<h2>Regional Legal, Justice and Counselling Services</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.empoweringchange.net/\">Central Okanagan Elizabeth Fry Society</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kamloopsefry.com/\">Kamloops Elizabeth Fry and Housing Society</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.pawc.ca/\">Penticton and Area Women’s Centre</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://pgefry.bc.ca/\">Prince George and District Elizabeth Fry Society</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sovas.ca/\">South Okanagan Victim Assistance Society</a>\r\n<h2>Provincial and National Resources</h2>\r\n<h5><a href=\"http://www.bchousing.org/Find/Fleeing_Abuse\">BC Housing (Transition Houses in BC)</a></h5>\r\n<h5><a href=\"http://www.bchrt.bc.ca\">BC Human Rights Tribunal</a></h5>\r\n<h5><a href=\"http://bcsth.ca/\">BC Society for Transition Houses (BCSTH)</a>\r\n<a href=\" http://www.pssg.gov.bc.ca/victimservices/financial/index.htm\">Crime Victim Assistance Program – Ministry of Justice</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.elizabethfry.ca/\">Canadian Association of Elizabeth Fry Societies</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.endingviolence.org/\">Community Coordination for Women’s Safety (CCWS)</a>\r\n<a href=\" http://www.endingviolence.org/\">Ending Violence Association of BC (EVA)</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.lawfoundationbc.org/\">Law Foundation of BC</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.lss.bc.ca/\">Legal Services Society of BC (LSS)</a></h5>\r\n<h5><a href=\"http://www.phac-aspc.gc.ca/sfv-avf/index.php\">Stop Family Violence</a></h5>\r\n<h5><a href=\"http://www.findsupportbc.com\">Find Support BC</a></h5>\r\n<h5>The Family Support Institute of BC has just launched their newest family support website.  This site is BC\'s first every user friendly, searchable database of disability related supports, services and community based activities for anyone in BC.</h5>\r\n<a title=\"Dial-A-Law\" href=\"http://www.dialalaw.org\" target=\"_blank\">Dial-A-Law</a>\r\nDial-A-Law is a library of free legal information in BC, prepared by lawyers.  It has practical information on over 130 legal topics in BC.  You can learn about legal rights and responsibilities, and the legal system.  Dial-A-Law transcripts are offered in English, Chinese and Punjabi.  Scripts are also available online in digital audio format.  Dial-A-Law is available in two ways - Telephone: <strong>604-687-4680</strong> or outside Greater Vancouver call <strong>1-800-565-5297</strong>; the Dial-A-Law website (link above).\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Lawyer Referral Service\" href=\"http://www.lrsbc.org\" target=\"_blank\">Lawyer Referral Service</a>\r\nThis service is designed to assist the general public in finding the appropriate lawyer.  The lawyer will provide up to a half hour consultation for $25 (plus tax).  This interview is to find out whether or not the caller has a legal problem.  If both parties agree to proceed with services, then they may do so at the lawyer\'s regular fee.  Telephone <strong>604-687-3221</strong> or <strong>Toll-Free: 1-800-663-1919</strong> (Monday to Friday from 8:30 am to 4:30 pm).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Links', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'links', '', '', '2016-09-14 22:02:53', '2016-09-14 22:02:53', '', 0, 'http://localhost/transition-house/?page_id=13', 0, 'page', '', 0),
