(60, 3, '2012-08-21 23:08:37', '2012-08-21 23:08:37', '<h1>Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling</h1>\r\nChildren who witness the abuse of their mother or serious family conflict live in fear and anxiety, waiting for the next violent episode to occur.\r\n\r\nWhile some children show clear signs, such as aggression or depression, other children display less obvious problems, such as poor attitudes about violence and poor problem-solving skills. Both types of children can benefit from a program specifically designed to meet their needs.\r\n\r\nOur program includes both individual and group counselling for children ages 3 to 18, as well as counselling, education, and support programs for parents.', 'Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'children-who-witness-abuse-counselling-vernon', '', '', '2016-08-30 17:25:15', '2016-08-30 17:25:15', '', 33, 'http://localhost/transition-house/?page_id=60', 0, 'page', '', 0),
