(288, 2, '2016-01-25 22:31:26', '2016-01-25 22:31:26', '<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-287\" title=\"Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling: Vernon\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/children_who_witness.jpg\" alt=\"Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling: Vernon\" width=\"304\" height=\"231\" />\n<h4><strong>For more information contact:</strong>\n<strong>Vernon Program</strong> 250-558-3850  ext. 201</h4>\n<h4><strong>Armstrong Program</strong> 250-546-6744</h4>\n<h4><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Children-who-witness-Abuse-brochure-2013.pdf\">VIEW BROCHURE</a></h4>', 'Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '60-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-01-25 22:31:26', '2016-01-25 22:31:26', '', 60, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2012/09/60-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1561, 2, '2016-01-25 22:31:48', '2016-01-25 22:31:48', '<h1>Oak Centre - Child and Youth Advocacy</h1>\r\nOak Centre is a warm and welcoming place where children and youth who have experienced abuse, sexual assault, or witnessed a crime such as domestic violence can be interviewed by the RCMP and child protection workers. The aim of Oak Centre is to minimize the trauma a child feels when disclosing abuse, assault, or speaking about what they may have witnessed. Our Child and Youth Advocate, located at Oak Centre, supports both the child and the caregivers throughout the process, ensuring they receive the supportive services they require along their journey to long-term healing.', 'Oak Centre - Child and Youth Advocacy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1558-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-25 22:31:48', '2016-01-25 22:31:48', '', 1558, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2016/01/1558-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(289, 3, '2012-09-07 21:50:07', '2012-09-07 21:50:07', '<h1>Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling: Vernon</h1>\r\nChildren who witness the abuse of their mother or serious family conflict live in fear and anxiety, waiting for the next violent episode to occur.\r\n\r\nWhile some children show clear signs, such as aggression or depression, other children display less obvious problems, such as poor attitudes about violence and poor problem-solving skills. Both types of children can benefit from a program specifically designed to meet their needs.\r\n\r\nOur program includes both individual and group counselling for children ages 3 to 18, as well as counselling, education, and support programs for parents.', 'Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling: Vernon', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-09-07 21:50:07', '2012-09-07 21:50:07', '', 60, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2012/09/60-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
