(1087, 2, '2014-08-05 22:57:55', '2014-08-05 22:57:55', '<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/BrookeArtDonation2014.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1084\" title=\"BrookeArtDonation2014\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/BrookeArtDonation2014-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Photo by Lisa McMullin</em>.\r\n\r\nBrooke McLardy (Left), VWTHS Programs Director with her artist-teacher Linda Hunt (Right) and their painting titled <strong><em>\"Transition\"</em> </strong>which was auctioned off for $850.<em> </em>\r\n\r\nA total of <strong>$8,457.60</strong> was raised through at the first annual charity event held by <em>The Rise Community Association</em> (RCA) held on July 5, 2014 on Johnny\'s Patio at The Rise.  Eleven pieces of art were auctioned off as was a furniture set donated by <em>Beachcomber Home Leisure</em>.  All of the money raised will be used to purchase new beds for the Transition House.\r\n\r\nNewspaper Articles:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vernonmorningstar.com/entertainment/263553811.html\">http://www.vernonmorningstar.com/entertainment/263553811.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vernonmorningstar.com/entertainment/266299251.html\">http://www.vernonmorningstar.com/entertainment/266299251.html</a>', 'THE RISE COMMUNITY ASSOCIATION - First Annual Charity Event', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1083-autosave', '', '', '2014-08-05 22:57:55', '2014-08-05 22:57:55', '', 1083, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2014/08/1083-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1086, 2, '2014-08-05 20:52:46', '2014-08-05 20:52:46', '<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/BrookeArtDonation2014.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1084\" title=\"BrookeArtDonation2014\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/BrookeArtDonation2014-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Photo by Lisa McMullin</em>.\r\n\r\nBrooke McLardy (Left), VWTHS Programs Director with her artist-teacher Linda Hunt (Right) and their painting titled \"Transition\" which was auctioned off for $850.<em> </em>\r\n\r\nThe Vernon Women\'s Transition House Society gratefully accepted a donation for<em> $8,457.60</em> from <em>The Rise Community Association</em> (RCA) for the purchase of new beds for the Transition House.  The funds were raised at the RCA\'s first annual charity event.  The RCA paired local artists and local celebrities to create a piece of art to auction off at the event held July 5, 2014 on Johnny\'s Patio at The Rise.  Eleven pieces of art were auctioned off as was a furniture set donated by Beachcomber Home Leisure.', 'DONATION - The Rise Community Association', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1083-revision-2', '', '', '2014-08-05 20:52:46', '2014-08-05 20:52:46', '', 1083, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2014/08/1083-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
