(452, 3, '2012-09-11 02:37:07', '2012-09-11 02:37:07', '<h1>Support to Young Parents</h1>\r\nThe Support to Young Parents Program provides affordable housing and support to pregnant and parenting teens and young women (ages 15-24).\r\n<h2>The services include:</h2>\r\n• One or two bedroom apartment with affordable rent.\r\n• Free utilities, laundry and cable.\r\n• Security system and monitoring.\r\n• Furniture and household items are available on a limited basis.', 'Support to Young Parents', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '49-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-09-11 02:37:07', '2012-09-11 02:37:07', '', 49, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2012/09/49-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1085, 2, '2014-08-05 20:52:25', '2014-08-05 20:52:25', '<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/BrookeArtDonation2014.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1084\" title=\"BrookeArtDonation2014\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/BrookeArtDonation2014-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\n\n<em>Photo by Lisa McMullin</em>.\n\nBrooke McLardy (Left), VWTHS Programs Director with her artist-teacher Linda Hunt (Right) and their painting titled \"Transition\" which was auctioned off for $850.<em> </em>\n\nThe Vernon Women\'s Transition House Society gratefully accepted a donation for $8,457.60 from The Rise Community Association (RCA) for the purchase of new beds for the Transition House.  The funds were raised at the RCA\'s first annual charity event.  The RCA paired local artists and local celebrities to create a piece of art to auction off at the event held July 5, 2014 on Johnny\'s Patio at The Rise.  Eleven pieces of art were auctioned off as was a furniture set donated by Beachcomber Home Leisure.', 'DONATION - The Rise Community Association', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1083-revision', '', '', '2014-08-05 20:52:25', '2014-08-05 20:52:25', '', 1083, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2014/08/1083-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(454, 3, '2012-09-11 01:57:12', '2012-09-11 01:57:12', '<h1>Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling: Vernon</h1>\r\nChildren who witness the abuse of their mother or serious family conflict live in fear and anxiety, waiting for the next violent episode to occur.\r\n\r\nWhile some children show clear signs, such as aggression or depression, other children display less obvious problems, such as poor attitudes about violence and poor problem-solving skills. Both types of children can benefit from a program specifically designed to meet their needs.\r\n\r\nOur program includes both individual and group counselling for children ages 3 to 18, as well as counselling, education, and support programs for parents.', 'Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling: Vernon', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-09-11 01:57:12', '2012-09-11 01:57:12', '', 60, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2012/09/60-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
