(506, 3, '2012-10-29 17:39:44', '2012-10-29 17:39:44', '<h1>Legal Advocacy Program</h1>\r\nAn advocate may help you understand information on:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>your rights and options</li>\r\n	<li>reconsideration requests</li>\r\n	<li>tribunals</li>\r\n	<li>procedures and investigations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAn advocate may also:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>provide information and referrals</li>\r\n	<li>help with writing letters, applications and forms</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>A legal advocate cannot give legal advice.</strong>', 'Legal Advocacy Program', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '67-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-10-29 17:39:44', '2012-10-29 17:39:44', '', 67, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2012/10/67-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(460, 3, '2012-10-26 18:37:40', '2012-10-26 18:37:40', '<h1>Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling: Vernon</h1>\r\nChildren who witness the abuse of their mother or serious family conflict live in fear and anxiety, waiting for the next violent episode to occur.\r\n\r\nWhile some children show clear signs, such as aggression or depression, other children display less obvious problems, such as poor attitudes about violence and poor problem-solving skills. Both types of children can benefit from a program specifically designed to meet their needs.\r\n\r\nOur program includes both individual and group counselling for children ages 3 to 18, as well as counselling, education, and support programs for parents.', 'Children Who Witness Abuse Counselling: Vernon', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-10-26 18:37:40', '2012-10-26 18:37:40', '', 60, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2012/10/60-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
