(848, 3, '2012-10-26 18:19:09', '2012-10-26 18:19:09', '<h1>Women’s Counselling: Vernon</h1>\r\nWe offer free, accessible and confidential counselling services to women who have experienced violence or abuse. We work to assist women in their healing with support, awareness and education.\r\n\r\nThe counselling services available focus on the needs of the woman. We regard her safety and that of her children as paramount.\r\n<h2>Services we offer:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Confidential individual and/or group counselling services to women based on the needs of women</li>\r\n	<li>A safe environment to look at personal safety, feelings and the effects of abuse</li>\r\n	<li>Support, information and encouragement to help women discover their strengths</li>\r\n	<li>Referral services to other support agencies that will help women in their recovery process</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Women’s Counselling: Vernon', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '43-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-10-26 18:19:09', '2012-10-26 18:19:09', '', 43, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2012/10/43-revision-10/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(944, 2, '2014-04-07 17:26:26', '2014-04-07 17:26:26', '<em>Article by Jennifer Smith, Morning Star Staff</em>\n\nThe community is urged to step forward and take action against violence.\n\nDomestic violence unfortunately continues to be a reality, therefore, in conjunction with National Victims of Crime Awareness Week, which starts today,m a special presentation is taking place Thursday called Unite to End Violence.\n\nRiminder Gakhal will be a keynote speaker at the forum, which takes place from 6 p.m. to 8 p.m. at the Schubert Centre.  It was 18 years ago, almost to the day, that nine members of the Gakhal and Saran families were murdered by the husband of one of the women.\n\nAlong with the presentation, Transition House will have an information table set up at the Village Green Centre Monday through Thursday.\n\n\"Sombody will be there to talk about services provided for victims of crime,\" said Allison Briggs, Awareness and Special Events Coordinator, noting that anyone can also call the Crisis Line toll free at 1-888-353-CARE (2273).\n\n\"There\'s always violence going on but I\'m hoping people are becoming more aware and help,\" said Briggs.\n\n\"It\'s our job as a community to gather together and try to help them.  It\'s about ending violence and supporting people.\"\n\nWhile the Gakhal family has previously held a vigil to remember the 1996 murders, they mourned in private this year.', 'DOMESTIC VIOLENCE AWARENESS URGED', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '942-revision-2', '', '', '2014-04-07 17:26:26', '2014-04-07 17:26:26', '', 942, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2014/04/942-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(945, 2, '2014-04-07 17:28:30', '2014-04-07 17:28:30', '<em>Article by Jennifer Smith, Morning Star Staff</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>The community is urged to step forward and take action against violence</strong>.\r\n\r\nDomestic violence unfortunately continues to be a reality, therefore, in conjunction with <em><strong>National Victims of Crime Awareness Week</strong></em>, which starts today, a special presentation is taking place Thursday, April 10th, called <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em><strong>Unite to End Violence</strong></em></span>.\r\n\r\nRiminder Gakhal will be a keynote speaker at the forum, which takes place from 6 p.m. to 8 p.m. at the Schubert Centre.  It was 18 years ago, almost to the day, that nine members of the Gakhal and Saran families were murdered by the husband of one of the women.\r\n\r\nAlong with the presentation, Transition House will have an information table set up at the Village Green Centre Monday through Thursday.\r\n\r\n\"<em>Sombody will be there to talk about services provided for victims of crime,\"</em> said Allison Briggs, Awareness and Special Events Coordinator, noting that anyone can also call the <strong>Crisis Line</strong> toll free at <strong>1-888-353-CARE (2273).</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>\"There\'s always violence going on but I\'m hoping people are becoming more aware and help,\"</em> said Briggs.\r\n\r\n<em>\"It\'s our job as a community to gather together and try to help them.  It\'s</em> <em>about ending violence and supporting people.\"</em>\r\n\r\nWhile the Gakhal family has previously held a vigil to remember the 1996 murders, they mourned in private this year.', 'DOMESTIC VIOLENCE AWARENESS URGED', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '942-revision-3', '', '', '2014-04-07 17:28:30', '2014-04-07 17:28:30', '', 942, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2014/04/942-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
