(1314, 2, '2015-04-20 18:49:17', '2015-04-20 18:49:17', '<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/CommunityPaintingProject20151.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-1311 aligncenter\" title=\"CommunityPaintingProject2015\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/CommunityPaintingProject20151-300x182.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"182\" /></a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><em>Thoughts on Art Project...</em></strong></p>\r\nThis past winter the residents of the Vernon Women\'s Transition House participated in a Community Painting Project.  I was one of four women who chose to open myself up to finding ways of sharing my story through art.  When I initially heard about it I was quite excited to participate and find a creative outlet to express the emotional impact abuse had on me.  I found that despite the diverse background of the participants we had the shared experience of being survivors, and through this we became one voice.  I think it is so important to ensure that our voices are heard; the public needs to know domestic violence affects us all, regardless of what community you\'re from, or what age or race you are.  The project afforded me the opportunity to safely express what I was feeling and to communicate how abuse has affected me.  Painting also allowed me to reconnect with my artistic side and see something positive that we all worked together to complete.  Every week I found myself looking forward to working on this project, which motivated me to keep fighting, and for that, I cannot thank the organizers enough.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Community Painting Project Participant</p>', 'COMMUNITY PAINTING PROJECT', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1309-revision-3', '', '', '2015-04-20 18:49:17', '2015-04-20 18:49:17', '', 1309, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2015/04/1309-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1242, 2, '2015-03-02 19:00:31', '2015-03-02 19:00:31', '<em>Morning Star Staff - Sunday, March 1, 2015</em>\n\nVernon residents are being urged to honour those special women in their lives. \n\nAn <strong>International Women\'s Day</strong> celebration in support of <strong>Vernon Women\'s Transition House Soci</strong>ety will be held March 8th at the Schubert Centre from 2 to 4 p.m.  \"This event will bring together the community to commemorate the amazing women in all of our lives,\" siad Rosalie Paquette, the Society\'s Awareness and Special Events Coordinator.\n\nThis celebration is for all ages, women and men alike, and will feature an amazing group of guests speakers as well as live music from women in our very own community.  Refreshments will be provided, as well as some amazing door prizes.\"\n\nAll proceeds from entry donations (suggested $5 minimum) will go directly to <strong>Transition House</strong>.\n\nthe Society provides safety and shelter for women and children fleeing abuse.  It also offers women\'s outreach and counselling. \n\nThis year, take some time to come together for international Women\'s Day and celebrate your mother, sister, wife, and friends,\" said Paquette.', 'WOMEN\'S DAY HELPS TRANSITION HOUSE', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1239-autosave', '', '', '2015-03-02 19:00:31', '2015-03-02 19:00:31', '', 1239, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2015/03/1239-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
