(1313, 2, '2015-04-20 18:48:35', '2015-04-20 18:48:35', '&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/CommunityPaintingProject20151.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-1311 aligncenter\" title=\"CommunityPaintingProject2015\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/CommunityPaintingProject20151-300x182.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"182\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><em>Thoughts on Art Project...</em></strong></p>\nThis past winter the residents of the Vernon Women\'s Transition House participated in a Community Painting Project.  I was one of four women who chose to open myself up to finding ways of sharing my story through art.  When I initially heard about it I was quite excited to participate and find a creative outlet to express the emotional impact abuse had on me.  I found that despite the diverse background of the participants we had the shared experience of being survivors, and through this we became one voice.  I think it is so important to ensure that our voices are heard; the public needs to know domestic violence affects us all, regardless of what community you\'re from, or what age or race you are.  The project afforded me the opportunity to safely express what I was feeling and to communicate how abuse has affected me.  Painting also allowed me to reconnect with my artistic side and see something positive that we all worked together to complete.  Every week I found myself looking forward to working on this project, which motivated me to keep fighting, and for that, I cannot thank the organizers enough.\n\nVWTHS Resident', 'COMMUNITY PAINTING PROJECT', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1309-revision-2', '', '', '2015-04-20 18:48:35', '2015-04-20 18:48:35', '', 1309, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2015/04/1309-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
