(1239, 2, '2015-03-02 18:04:43', '2015-03-02 18:04:43', '<em>Morning Star Staff - Sunday, March 1, 2015</em>\r\n\r\nVernon residents are being urged to honour those special women in their lives. \r\n\r\nAn <strong>International Women\'s Day</strong> celebration in support of <strong>Vernon Women\'s Transition House Society</strong> will be held <strong>March 8th</strong> at the <strong>Schubert Centre from 2 to 4 p.m.</strong>  \"This event will bring together the community to commemorate the amazing women in all of our lives,\" siad Rosalie Paquette, the Society\'s Awareness and Special Events Coordinator.\r\n\r\nThis celebration is for all ages, women and men alike, and will feature an amazing group of guests speakers as well as live music from women in our very own community.  Refreshments will be provided, as well as some amazing door prizes.\"\r\n\r\nAll proceeds from entry donations (suggested $5 minimum) will go directly to <strong>Transition House</strong>.\r\n\r\nthe Society provides safety and shelter for women and children fleeing abuse.  It also offers women\'s outreach and counselling. \r\n\r\nThis year, take some time to come together for international Women\'s Day and celebrate your mother, sister, wife, and friends,\" said Paquette.', 'WOMEN\'S DAY HELPS TRANSITION HOUSE', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'womens-day-helps-transition-house', '', '', '2015-03-02 19:01:14', '2015-03-02 19:01:14', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=1239', 0, 'post', '', 0),
