(1266, 2, '2015-03-17 20:40:42', '2015-03-17 20:40:42', '<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Playhouse.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1265\" title=\"Playhouse\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Playhouse-300x259.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"259\" /></a>\n\n<strong>Playhouses are being auctioned off as a fundraiser, sponsored by the Village Green Centre.</strong>\n\n<em>Vernon Morning Star - Sunday, March 15, 2015</em>\n\nThis spring, the Village Green Centre will launch its <em><strong>Houses for Hope campaign</strong></em>. \n\nThe goal is to raise money and awareness for the <em><strong>Vernon Women\'s Transition House Society. </strong></em> Ten, four-foot-by-four-foot-by-five-foot playhouses have been constructed by Vernon-based Creative Connectors.\n\n\"The undecorated play-houses will each be pre-sold to campaign sponsors for $500 each, with all net proceeds going directly to the Transition House,\" said Darren Robinson, Marketing Manager.  \"Each sponsor will then be given three weeks to decorate, paint and/or furnish the playhouses to their liking before they are returned to Village Green Centre where they will be on display for public viewing from April 10th to 26th.\"\n\nShoppers will be given the opportunity to bid on their favourite playhouse via the 16-day siletn auction.  there will also be a people\'s choice award of $150 in Village Green Centre gift cards for the sponsor with the most popular finished playhouse.\n\nThe Vernon Women\'s Transition House Society provides safety, shelter, counselling, and outreach for women and children fleeing abuse.', 'HOUSES BUILD HOPE FOR WOMEN', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1264-revision', '', '', '2015-03-17 20:40:42', '2015-03-17 20:40:42', '', 1264, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2015/03/1264-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1002, 2, '2014-01-13 18:59:01', '2014-01-13 18:59:01', '<h2><span style=\"color: #7d3a46;\"><strong>THANK YOU TO VERNON AND DISTRICT WOMEN\'S CENTRE</strong>:</span></h2>\r\nIt was a bittersweet moment.\r\n\r\nWe were gifted with a significant donation for the women and children we serve but it came at the cost of a local agency.\r\n\r\nThe Vernon and District Women\'s Centre closed its doors in May 2011.\r\n\r\nThe board has remained active and hopeful that the political climate would change and funding to continue their work with vulnerable women in our community could continue.\r\n\r\nThis, unfortunately, has not been the case.\r\n\r\nThe board of the Women\'s Centre is preparing to dissolve and in doing so has generously gifted their remaining funds to continue to assist women and children.\r\n\r\nWe extend a heartfelt thank you to the board for this meaningful gift with we plan to put towards running groups for women who have experienced violence, mental ill health and substance use issues and to continue our work to prevent violence against women and children in our community.\r\n\r\nAgain, <em>Thank you.</em>\r\n\r\nBrooke McLardy, Programs Director and Ninke Beeksma, Executive Director - Vernon Women\'s Transition House Society', 'THANK YOU', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '876-revision-3', '', '', '2014-01-13 18:59:01', '2014-01-13 18:59:01', '', 876, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2014/01/876-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
