(1312, 2, '2015-04-20 18:46:09', '2015-04-20 18:46:09', '&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThis past winter the residents of the Vernon Women\'s Transition House participated in a Community Painting Project.  I was one of four women who chose to open myself up to finding ways of sharing my story through art.  When I initially heard about it I was quite excited to participate and find a creative outlet to express the emotional impact abuse had on me.  I found that despite the diverse background of the participants we had the shared experience of being survivors, and through this we became one voice.  I think it is so important to ensure that our voices are heard; the public needs to know domestic violence affects us all, regardless of what community you\'re from, or what age or race you are.  The project afforded me the opportunity to safely express what I was feeling and to communicate how abuse has affected me.  Painting also allowed me to reconnect with my artistic side and see something positive that we all worked together to complete.  Every week I found myself looking forward to working on this project, which motivated me to keep fighting, and for t', 'COMMUNITY PAINTING PROJECT', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1309-revision', '', '', '2015-04-20 18:46:09', '2015-04-20 18:46:09', '', 1309, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2015/04/1309-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1267, 2, '2015-03-17 20:41:09', '2015-03-17 20:41:09', '<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Playhouse.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1265\" title=\"Playhouse\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Playhouse-300x259.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"259\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Playhouses are being auctioned off as a fundraiser, sponsored by the Village Green Centre.</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Vernon Morning Star - Sunday, March 15, 2015</em>\r\n\r\nThis spring, the Village Green Centre will launch its <em><strong>Houses for Hope campaign</strong></em>. \r\n\r\nThe goal is to raise money and awareness for the <em><strong>Vernon Women\'s Transition House Society. </strong></em> Ten, four-foot-by-four-foot-by-five-foot playhouses have been constructed by Vernon-based Creative Connectors.\r\n\r\n\"The undecorated play-houses will each be pre-sold to campaign sponsors for $500 each, with all net proceeds going directly to the Transition House,\" said Darren Robinson, Marketing Manager.  \"Each sponsor will then be given three weeks to decorate, paint and/or furnish the playhouses to their liking before they are returned to Village Green Centre where they will be on display for public viewing from April 10th to 26th.\"\r\n\r\nShoppers will be given the opportunity to bid on their favourite playhouse via the 16-day siletn auction.  there will also be a people\'s choice award of $150 in Village Green Centre gift cards for the sponsor with the most popular finished playhouse.\r\n\r\nThe Vernon Women\'s Transition House Society provides safety, shelter, counselling, and outreach for women and children fleeing abuse.', 'HOUSES BUILD HOPE FOR WOMEN', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1264-revision-2', '', '', '2015-03-17 20:41:09', '2015-03-17 20:41:09', '', 1264, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2015/03/1264-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
